.TH TRYFOREVER "1" "December 2025" "202602020740-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
tryforever \- Keep an app running until it successfully completes
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tryforever
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,COMMAND\/\fR] [\fI\,ARGUMENTS\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B tryforever
is a script that repeatedly runs a command until it exits successfully (exit code 0). It is useful for commands that may fail intermittently.
.PP
The script will keep retrying the command with optional delays between attempts.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Display help message with usage information and available options
.TP
.BR \-\-config
Generate or regenerate user configuration file with default settings
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show script version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-options
Display all available command-line options
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable debug mode with verbose output and command tracing (set -x)
.TP
.BR \-\-raw
Disable colorized output for plain text display
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B tryforever curl http://example.com
Keep trying until curl succeeds
.TP
.B tryforever --delay 5 wget file.zip
Retry with 5 second delay
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.config/myscripts/tryforever/settings.conf
User configuration file for tryforever preferences
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success (command completed successfully)
.TP
.B 1
General error
.SH NOTES
.IP \(bu 2
Retries until success
.IP \(bu 2
Configurable delay between attempts
.IP \(bu 2
Useful for intermittent failures
